  "prompt": "How are style fonts added to an MIT app inventor?",
  "response": "In MIT App Inventor, you can change the font style of text displayed in components such as **Labels**, **Buttons**, and **TextBoxes** by using the properties panel. However, MIT App Inventor does not natively support custom font files (e.g., `.ttf` or `.otf` files). Instead, you can select from a limited set of predefined font styles.\n\n### Steps to Change Font Style in MIT App Inventor:\n1. **Select the Component**:\n   - In the Designer view, click on the component (e.g., Label, Button) where you want to change the font style.\n\n2. **Navigate to the Properties Panel**:\n   - On the right side of the Designer, you\u2019ll see the **Properties** panel for the selected component.\n\n3. **Change the Font Property**:\n   - Look for the `Font` property in the Properties panel. Click on it to see the available options.\n   - The default options include **Default**, **Sans Serif**, **Serif**, **Monospace**, and a few others.\n\n4. **Preview the Change**:\n   - The font style of the component will update immediately in the Designer view.\n\n### Limitations:\n- **Predefined Fonts Only**: You cannot upload custom fonts to MIT App Inventor. You are limited to the built-in font options.\n- **Platform Differences**: Fonts may appear slightly different on Android devices depending on the device\u2019s operating system and settings.\n\n### Workarounds for Custom Fonts:\nIf you need to use a specific custom font that is not available in the predefined options, consider the following workarounds:\n1. **Image-Based Text**: Create the text with your desired font in an image editor (e.g., Photoshop, Canva) and use an **Image** or **Canvas** component to display the text as an image.\n2. **WebView Component**: Use the **WebView** component to display HTML/CSS content where you can define custom fonts. This requires hosting the font file online and linking it in your HTML.\n\n### Example of Using WebView for Custom Fonts:\n1. Host your custom `.ttf` or `.otf` font file on a web server.\n2. Add a **WebView** component to your app.\n3. Use the WebView\u2019s `HomeUrl` property to load an HTML file that includes the custom font via CSS.\n\nFor example, the HTML file might look like this:\n```html\n<style>\n  @font-face {\n    font-family: 'CustomFont';\n    src: url('https://your-server.com/path-to-font/CustomFont.ttf');\n  }\n  body {\n    font-family: 'CustomFont', sans-serif;\n  }\n</style>\n<p>This is custom font text.</p>\n```\n\nWhile MIT App Inventor\u2019s font options are limited, these workarounds can help you achieve a more customized look if needed.",
